content: Sifting through my notes from Japan. Realizing that a trip to the temple inspired some new risk management ideas. Might incorporate that into my trading algo.
Just secured an interview with a quant firm specializing in AI-driven strategies. Fingers crossed, but also learning so much from their website alone.
Diving into AI-driven software environments. They're a maze but I'm starting to get the hang of it. Feels like learning a new language.
Setback: My trading algorithm isn't performing as expected. Back to the drawing board to refine the market analysis component.
Had a coffee with a mentor from my internship. His insights on market behavior are gold. We're planning a regular catch-up to brainstorm.
Birthday reflections: 22 feels like a turning point. All the global experiences are now feeding into my professional growth. Here's to new strategies and learning from past mistakes.
Progress! My trading algo is now incorporating some Thai-inspired risk management principles. Small steps, but I can feel the difference.
Interview prep has me studying AI trading strategies from the ground up. The more I learn, the more I see the potential in this field.
Networking event tonight. Met some fascinating people in the tech and trading scene. Exchanged contacts and ideas—it's all about connections.
Just got a second interview with the quant firm. They seem genuinely interested in my AI background. This could be the big break.
Realized that my coding skills need a boost. Enrolled in an advanced Python course to streamline my development process.
Another setback with the algo. It's humbling to see where I went wrong, but it's also a learning curve. Back to refining and testing.
Lunch with my mentor today. We talked about the balance between technology and human intuition in trading. He's pushing me to think deeper.
Got the job offer! I'm officially a quant trader with a focus on AI-driven strategies. The journey from Japan to here has been wild, but it's all coming together. Time to celebrate!
